The paper proposes a new method for estimating advantages in reinforcement learning, which is a core topic in machine learning. The paper also evaluates the proposed method on various benchmarks, including continuous control, locomotion, Atari games, and sparse-reward environments, which suggests that the paper could be relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. Based on these factors, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves image processing and computer vision techniques, which could make cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the impacts of different methods for estimating advantages, which could make cs.SY (Systems and Control) a relevant sub-category as well.
